Mortal Kombat — 10 Requirements

1. The game must display a character selection screen where the player chooses a fighter before the match begins.
2. The game must support 1v1 fighting matches with two health bars shown on the screen.
3. The player must control their fighter using movement inputs (left/right, crouch, jump) and attack inputs (punch/kick).
4. Each fighter must have at least one special move that can be triggered by a defined input combination.
5. The match must be won when the opponent’s health reaches zero, and the game must declare the round winner.
6. The game must use a best-of-three rounds format (first fighter to win 2 rounds wins the match).
7. A round timer must count down during each round; if time runs out, the fighter with more health must win the round.
8. The game must include a blocking/defense mechanic that reduces or prevents damage when used correctly.
9. The game must detect collisions/hits and apply damage and knockback effects based on the attack type.
10. When the match ends, the game must show an end-of-match screen and allow the player to restart or return to character select.
